cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with language representation models and cross-lingual transfer learning for reading comprehension tasks. It could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) as it involves training a model on a large corpus of data. Additionally, it could be categorized under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as it involves developing a model that can learn and generalize across multiple languages. It could also be categorized under cs.IR (Information Retrieval) as reading comprehension tasks involve retrieving information from text. Finally, it could be categorized under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) as it involves training a neural network model.
